{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491233","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491233"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:38:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:38:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"885"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"885","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/885"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.02,0.71,0.01,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"885"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103771"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"885","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/885"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"885"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86193"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"297"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"2888"},{"type":"tags","id":"4083"},{"type":"tags","id":"4100"},{"type":"tags","id":"4985"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"149"},{"type":"contributions","id":"150"},{"type":"contributions","id":"612"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10653"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10944"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37004"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38974"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43044"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45007"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103771","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/103771"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 50-year-old First Nations woman presents for a cervical screening test (CST). Her last CST was performed 2 years ago and was reported HPV detected (not 16/18) and possible low-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion (pLSIL). This latest test is again positive for HPV (not 16/18) and reflex cytology again demonstrates pLSIL.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Repeat CST in 12 months","Retest for reflex cytology in six weeks","Colposcopy","Retest for HPV in six weeks","Referral to a gynaecological oncologist"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis woman had a previous HPV detected (not 16/18) result and pLSIS on reflex cytology. The repeat test detected persisting HPV with pLSIL and patients who are low risk are recommended to return for \u003Cstrong\u003Erepeat CST in 12 months\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHowever, some groups of people may be at higher risk of high-grade abnormality and should be \u003Cstrong\u003Ereferred for colposcopy\u003C/strong\u003E if HPV is detected at 12 months regardless of their cytology result. These include those who:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIdentify as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAre aged 50 years or older\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWere at least 2 years overdue for screening at the time of their initial screen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAs this woman is over 50 and identifies as Aboriginal, she needs referral for colposcopy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Eretest for reflex cytology in six weeks \u003C/strong\u003Eor a \u003Cstrong\u003Eretest for HPV in six weeks \u003C/strong\u003Eis undertaken when the respective tests yield unsatisfactory results. \u003Cstrong\u003EReferral to a gynaecological oncology specialist \u003C/strong\u003Ewithout prior colposcopy is inappropriate without further information, and may only serve to heighten this patient\u0027s anxiety which is common after an abnormal cervical screening test. Most hospitals have a colposcopy clinic which has short waitlists and easy access to specialist services as needed.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Women deemed to be at higher risk of high-grade abnormality should be referred for colposcopy if HPV is detected at 12 months regardless of cytology result.","Patients over the age of 50 or identify as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islanders or those who are over due for screening should be referred for Colposcopy","Patients with a HPV (not 16/18) positive result at 12-month follow up test are offered repeat CST at another 12-months as long as they are considered low-intermediate risk"],"references":["Department of Health and Aged Care. Important changes to the National Cervical Screening Program\u0027s Clinical Guidelines pathway for women at intermediate risk. Australian Government, Dept of Health and Aged Care; 2021. https://www.health.gov.au/news/important-changes-to-the-national-cervical-screening-programs-clinical-guidelines-pathway-for-women-at-intermediate-risk","Egemen, D., Cheung, L.C., Chen, X., Demarco, M., Perkins, R.B., Kinney, W., Poitras, N., Befano, B., Locke, A., Guido, R.S., Wiser, A.L., Gage, J.C., Katki, H.A., Wentzensen, N., Castle, P.E., Schiffman, M., Lorey, T.S., 2020. Risk Estimates Supporting the 2019 SCCP Risk-Based Management Consensus Guidelines. (J Low Genit Tract Dis 2020;24: 132\u2013143)","The Royal Australian and New Zealand College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists, 2020. Cervical cancer screening in Australia and New Zealand."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86193"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"885"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86193","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86193"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-26T18:54:27+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-26T18:55:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"885"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103771"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Unde